Frequency files
===============

Frequency counts for each language were obtained from the latest (2018-03-01) 
Wikipedia corpora provided by the Leipzig Corpora Collection (LCC). Corpus 
files contain 100K randomly sampled sentences from Wikipedia.

All corpora provided by LCC are licensed under CC BY and can be downloaded 
from Abteilung Automatische Sprachverarbeitung, Universit√§t Leipzig
(http://wortschatz.uni-leipzig.de/en/download)

Reference: 

D. Goldhahn, T. Eckart & U. Quasthoff: Building Large Monolingual Dictionaries 
at the Leipzig Corpora Collection: From 100 to 200 Languages. In: Proceedings 
of the 8th International Language Ressources and Evaluation (LREC'12), 2012.

Text samples
============

Sample files for key term extraction are obtained from Wikinews.